          "body": "The travel notes (vv.12-13) are not filler. Paul is establishing that the Cretan church will be evaluated by how it treats Zenas and Apollos passing through. *Diligently help* — *spoudaiōs propempson*, send them on equipped, lacking nothing. Then v.14 universalizes: *Our people must also learn to engage in good deeds to meet pressing needs, so that they will not be unfruitful (akarpoi).* The closing benediction *Grace be with you all* (v.15) returns the chapter to where the gospel hymn began. Grace saves (v.7); grace blesses (v.15); and between those two graces, the church is to be intentional, fruitful, and visible to a watching world."
